name: sarcosine oxidase
classes: Acting on the CH-NH group of donors;
reaction: sarcosine + H2O + O2 = glycine + formaldehyde + H2O2 [RN:R00610]
comment: A flavoprotein (FAD). The flavin is both covalently and non-covalently bound in a molar ratio of 1:1.

references.title: Corynebacterium sarcosine oxidase: a unique enzyme having covalently-bound and noncovalently-bound flavins.
